            "suggestion": "Ensure 'authorized user' is defined in a shared glossary or cross-cutting access-control requirement."
          }
        ],
        "rewrittenRequirement": "An authorized user shall be able to control the presenter light of a connected compatible appliance that provides this feature, so that the user can switch the presenter light between active and inactive states from the appliance detail context in the app. The presenter light refers to the appliance light feature used to illuminate or present the stored wine.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Given a connected compatible appliance has a presenter light, when the user views the appliance detail context, then the user can see whether the presenter light is currently active or inactive.\n- Given the presenter light is inactive, when the user chooses to activate it, then the presenter light state becomes active and this state is visible to the user.\n- Given the presenter light is active, when the user chooses to deactivate it, then the presenter light state becomes inactive and this state is visible to the user.\n- Given a connected appliance does not provide a presenter light feature, when the user views the appliance detail context, then presenter light control is not presented as an available capability."
      }
