          "Given the appliance status model reports a normal or available state, when the dashboard is displayed, then the dashboard shows a state distinguishable as normal or available.",
          "Given the appliance status model reports an attention, warning, issue, or similar non-normal state, when the dashboard is displayed, then the dashboard shows a state distinguishable from normal or available.",
          "Given the user changes the selected appliance, when the dashboard context changes, then the displayed status updates to the status of the newly selected appliance."
        ],
        "exceptionFlows": [
          "Given the overall appliance status cannot be retrieved, calculated, or mapped to the product-defined status model, when the dashboard is displayed, then the dashboard shows a clear unknown or unavailable status and does not show normal or available by default."
