        "rowNumber": 2,
        "choice": "ai",
        "text": "A user viewing an appliance in the app dashboard shall be able to identify the appliance type of the currently selected appliance so that they can confirm they are viewing the correct appliance category.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Given a user has access to an appliance, when the user opens the app dashboard for that appliance, then the dashboard displays the appliance type.\n- The displayed appliance type corresponds to the currently selected appliance and uses the product-defined appliance type name.\n- If the appliance type cannot be determined, the dashboard clearly indicates that the appliance type is unavailable instead of showing an incorrect or blank value.",
        "excluded": false
      },
      {
        "rowNumber": 3,
        "choice": "ai",
        "text": "A user viewing an appliance in the app dashboard shall be able to see the current overall status of the currently selected appliance so that they can quickly understand whether the appliance requires attention.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Given a user has access to an appliance, when the user opens the app dashboard for that appliance, then the dashboard displays the appliance's current overall status.\n- The displayed status is based on the product-defined appliance status model, including at minimum a distinguishable normal/available state and a state indicating that attention or an issue may be present, if such a state applies to the appliance.\n- If the appliance status cannot be determined, the dashboard clearly indicates that the status is unavailable or unknown instead of showing a misleading normal status.\n- The status shown on the dashboard corresponds to the currently selected appliance.",
        "excluded": false
      },
