        "text": "An authorized user shall be able to set the target temperature, in degrees Celsius, for each available wine zone of a connected compatible appliance from the appliance detail page in the app. The allowed target temperature range shall be 5°C to 20°C inclusive, selectable only in 1°C increments.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Given a compatible appliance with one or more wine zones is available to the user, when the user opens the appliance detail page, then each available wine zone offers target temperature values from 5°C through 20°C inclusive.\n- Given the user selects a target temperature for a wine zone, when the value is within 5°C to 20°C and in a 1°C increment, then the selected value is accepted as the target temperature for that zone.\n- Given the user attempts to choose or enter a value below 5°C, above 20°C, or not in a 1°C increment, then that value is not accepted as a valid target temperature.\n- Given multiple wine zones exist, when the user changes the target temperature of one zone, then the change applies to that selected zone only.",
